com.github.wuic.engine.core

Class AbstractCompressorEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.wuic.engine.Engine
      • com.github.wuic.engine.NodeEngine
        • com.github.wuic.engine.core.AbstractCompressorEngine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Pipe.Transformer<ConvertibleNut>, Comparable<Engine>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImageCompressorEngine

    public abstract class AbstractCompressorEngine
extends NodeEngine
implements Pipe.Transformer<ConvertibleNut>

    This engine defines the base treatments to execute when compressing a set of files. It could be extended by different sub-classes which provide compression support.

    The compression is never performed if the doCompression flag is set to true.

    Since:
    0.1.0

      • canAggregateTransformedStream

        public boolean canAggregateTransformedStream()

        Indicates if the content generated when Pipe.Transformer.transform(InputStream, OutputStream, Object) is called can be aggregated to an other one. This is usually the case but won't be possible for instance when a magic number should appears only at the beginning of the composite stream and not in each stream of the aggregation.

        Specified by:
        canAggregateTransformedStream in interface Pipe.Transformer<ConvertibleNut>
        Returns:
        true if aggregation is possible, false otherwise
